Math.abs.description: Returns the absolute (positive) value of the input.

Math.acos.description: Returns the arccosine (inverse cosine) of a number, in radians.

Math.asin.description: Returns the arcsine (inverse sine) of a number, in radians.

Math.atan.description: Returns the arctangent (inverse tangent) of a number, in radians.

Math.atan2.description: Returns the arctangent of the quotient of its arguments, in radians.

Math.ceil.description: Returns the smallest integer greater than or equal to the input.

Math.cos.description: Returns the cosine of the input, in radians.

Math.exp.description: Returns Euler's number raised to the power of the input.

Math.floor.description: Returns the largest integer less than or equal to the input.

Math.log.description: Returns the natural logarithm (base e) of the input.

Math.max.description: Returns the largest of zero or more numbers.

Math.min.description: Returns the smallest of zero or more numbers.

Math.pow.description: Returns the base raised to the exponent power.

Math.random.description: Returns a pseudo-random number between 0 (inclusive) and 1 (exclusive).

Math.round.description: Returns the value of the input rounded to the nearest integer.

Math.sin.description: Returns the sine of the input, in radians.

Math.sqrt.description: Returns the square root of the input.

Math.tan.description: Returns the tangent of the input, in radians.

Math.E.description: Euler's number, the base of natural logarithms.

Math.PI.description: The ratio of the circumference of a circle to its diameter.

Date.now.description: Returns the number of milliseconds elapsed since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

Date.parse.description: Parses a date string and returns the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

Date.UTC.description: Returns the number of milliseconds between January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC and a specified date.

Date.constructor.description: Creates a new Date object representing a specific date and time.

Date.toString.description: Returns a string representation of the Date object.

Date.toDateString.description: Returns the date portion of the Date object as a human-readable string.

Date.toTimeString.description: Returns the time portion of the Date object as a human-readable string.

Date.toISOString.description: Returns a string in ISO 8601 format representing the Date object.

Date.toUTCString.description: Returns a string representation of the Date object in UTC time.

Date.toGMTString.description: Returns a string representation of the Date object in GMT time (deprecated).

Date.getDate.description: Returns the day of the month for the Date object.

Date.setDate.description: Sets the day of the month for the Date object.

Date.getDay.description: Returns the day of the week for the Date object (0 for Sunday, 6 for Saturday).

Date.getFullYear.description: Returns the year of the Date object.

Date.setFullYear.description: Sets the year for the Date object.

Date.getHours.description: Returns the hour (0–23) of the Date object.

Date.setHours.description: Sets the hour for the Date object.

Date.getMilliseconds.description: Returns the milliseconds (0–999) of the Date object.

Date.setMilliseconds.description: Sets the milliseconds for the Date object.

Date.getMinutes.description: Returns the minutes (0–59) of the Date object.

Date.setMinutes.description: Sets the minutes for the Date object.

Date.getMonth.description: Returns the month (0–11) of the Date object.

Date.setMonth.description: Sets the month for the Date object.

Date.getSeconds.description: Returns the seconds (0–59) of the Date object.

Date.setSeconds.description: Sets the seconds for the Date object.

Date.getTime.description: Returns the numeric value of the Date object as the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

Date.setTime.description: Sets the time for the Date object as the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

Date.getTimezoneOffset.description: Returns the difference in minutes between the local time zone and UTC.

Date.getUTCDate.description: Returns the day of the month (1–31) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.setUTCDate.description: Sets the day of the month (1–31) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.getUTCDay.description: Returns the day of the week (0–6) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.getUTCFullYear.description: Returns the full year (including century) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.setUTCFullYear.description: Sets the full year (including century) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.getUTCHours.description: Returns the hour (0–23) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.setUTCHours.description: Sets the hour (0–23) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.getUTCMilliseconds.description: Returns the milliseconds (0–999) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.setUTCMilliseconds.description: Sets the milliseconds (0–999) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.getUTCMinutes.description: Returns the minutes (0–59) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.setUTCMinutes.description: Sets the minutes (0–59) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.getUTCMonth.description: Returns the month (0–11) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.setUTCMonth.description: Sets the month (0–11) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.getUTCSeconds.description: Returns the seconds (0–59) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.setUTCSeconds.description: Sets the seconds (0–59) for the Date object in UTC time.

Date.valueOf.description: Returns the primitive value of the Date object as the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.

Date.getYear.description: Returns the year minus 1900 for the Date object (deprecated).

Date.setYear.description: Sets the year for the Date object, where the year is the number of years since 1900 (deprecated).

Date.toJSON.description: Returns a string representing the Date object for use in JSON encoding.

Date.toLocaleString.description: Returns a string representing the Date object in the local time zone.

Date.toLocaleDateString.description: Returns a string representing the date portion of the Date object in the local time zone.

Date.toLocaleTimeString.description: Returns a string representing the time portion of the Date object in the local time zone.

RegExp.constructor.description: Creates a new regular expression object. This method is the constructor for the RegExp object.

RegExp.exec.description: Executes a search for a match in a string. Returns an array of information or null if no match is found.

RegExp.compile.description: Re-compiles the regular expression with a new pattern and optional flags.

RegExp.toString.description: Returns a string representing the regular expression.

RegExp.test.description: Tests if a string matches a regular expression. Returns true if there's a match, false otherwise.

String.constructor.description: Creates a new string object from the given value. This method is the constructor for the String object.

String.anchor.description: Wraps the string in an HTML anchor tag with the specified name attribute.

String.at.description: Returns the character at the specified index (similar to charAt but works with code points).

String.big.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<big>` tag, making the text bigger.

String.blink.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<blink>` tag, making the text blink (deprecated).

String.bold.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<b>` tag, making the text bold.

String.charAt.description: Returns the character at the specified index in the string.

String.charCodeAt.description: Returns the Unicode value of the character at the specified index.

String.codePointAt.description: Returns the Unicode code point value of the character at the specified index, handling surrogate pairs.

String.concat.description: Combines two or more strings into one.

String.endsWith.description: Checks if the string ends with the specified substring.

String.fontcolor.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<font>` tag with a specified color.

String.fontsize.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<font>` tag with a specified size.

String.fixed.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<tt>` tag, making the text fixed-width.

String.includes.description: Checks if the string contains the specified substring.

String.indexOf.description: Returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified substring, or -1 if not found.

String.isWellFormed.description: Checks if the string is a well-formed Unicode string (no unpaired surrogate characters).

String.italics.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<i>` tag, making the text italic.

String.lastIndexOf.description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the specified substring, or -1 if not found.

String.link.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<a>` tag with the specified URL.

String.localeCompare.description: Compares two strings in the current locale, returning a number indicating the relative order of the strings.

String.match.description: Searches for a match between a regular expression and the string, returning an array of results.

String.matchAll.description: Returns an iterator for all matches of a regular expression in the string.

String.normalize.description: Returns the string in a normalized form (e.g., canonical equivalence).

String.padEnd.description: Pads the string with a specified string until it reaches a certain length, from the end.

String.padStart.description: Pads the string with a specified string until it reaches a certain length, from the start.

String.repeat.description: Returns a new string with the specified number of copies of the string.

String.replace.description: Replaces the first match of a substring or regular expression in the string with a new substring.

String.replaceAll.description: Replaces all matches of a substring or regular expression in the string with a new substring.

String.search.description: Searches for the first match of a regular expression in the string and returns its index.

String.slice.description: Extracts a section of the string and returns it as a new string.

String.small.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<small>` tag, making the text smaller.

String.split.description: Splits the string into an array of substrings, based on a specified delimiter.

String.strike.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<strike>` tag, striking through the text.

String.sub.description: Replicates the behavior of `substr` for older browsers (deprecated).

String.substr.description: Returns a substring of the string, starting from a specified index and optionally extending by a specified number of characters.

String.substring.description: Extracts characters from the string between two specified indices.

String.sup.description: Wraps the string in an HTML `<sup>` tag, making the text superscript.

String.startsWith.description: Checks if the string starts with the specified substring.

String.toString.description: Returns a string representation of the string object.

String.toWellFormed.description: Returns a well-formed version of the string (ensuring valid Unicode).

String.trim.description: Removes whitespace from both ends of the string.

String.trimStart.description: Removes whitespace from the beginning of the string.

String.trimLeft.description: Removes whitespace from the beginning of the string (alias for trimStart).

String.trimEnd.description: Removes whitespace from the end of the string.

String.trimRight.description: Removes whitespace from the end of the string (alias for trimEnd).

String.toLocaleLowerCase.description: Returns the string in lowercase, using the locale-specific case mappings.

String.toLocaleUpperCase.description: Returns the string in uppercase, using the locale-specific case mappings.

String.valueOf.description: Returns the primitive value of the string object.

Array.isArray.description: Checks if the value is an array.

Array.from.description: Creates a new array instance from an array-like or iterable object.

Array.fromAsync.description: Creates a new array from an asynchronous iterable object.
Array.fromAsync.example: async function* generate() { yield 1; yield 2; } Array.fromAsync(generate()) -> [1, 2]

Array.of.description: Creates a new array with a variable number of elements.

Array.constructor.description: Returns the constructor function for the array instance.

Array.at.description: Accesses the element at the specified index, supporting negative indexes.

Array.concat.description: Joins two or more arrays into a new array.

Array.copyWithin.description: Shallow copies part of the array to another location in the same array.

Array.fill.description: Fills all elements in the array with a specified value.

Array.find.description: Returns the first element in the array that satisfies a testing function.

Array.findIndex.description: Returns the index of the first element in the array that satisfies a testing function.

Array.findLast.description: Returns the last element in the array that satisfies a testing function.

Array.findLastIndex.description: Returns the index of the last element in the array that satisfies a testing function.

Array.lastIndexOf.description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of a specified element.

Array.pop.description: Removes the last element from the array and returns it.

Array.push.description: Adds one or more elements to the end of the array and returns the new length.

Array.reverse.description: Reverses the order of the elements in the array.

Array.shift.description: Removes the first element from the array and returns it.

Array.unshift.description: Adds one or more elements to the beginning of the array and returns the new length.

Array.slice.description: Returns a shallow copy of a portion of the array.

Array.sort.description: Sorts the elements of the array in place.

Array.splice.description: Changes the contents of the array by removing or replacing elements.

Array.includes.description: Checks if the array contains a specified element.

Array.indexOf.description: Returns the index of the first occurrence of a specified element.

Array.join.description: Joins the elements of the array into a single string, with an optional separator.

Array.keys.description: Returns a new array iterator object containing the keys (indices) of the array.

Array.entries.description: Returns a new array iterator object containing key-value pairs for each element.

Array.values.description: Returns a new array iterator object containing the values of the array.

Array.forEach.description: Executes a provided function once for each array element.

Array.filter.description: Creates a new array with all elements that pass a test.

Array.flat.description: Creates a new array with all sub-array elements concatenated.

Array.flatMap.description: First maps each element using a mapping function, then flattens the result into a new array.

Array.map.description: Creates a new array populated with the results of calling a function for every array element.

Array.every.description: Tests whether all elements in the array pass the test implemented by the provided function.

Array.some.description: Tests whether at least one element in the array passes the test implemented by the provided function.

Array.reduce.description: Applies a function against an accumulator and each element in the array to reduce it to a single value.

Array.reduceRight.description: Applies a function against an accumulator and each element in the array (from right to left).

Array.toReversed.description: Returns a new array with the elements in reverse order.

Array.toSorted.description: Returns a new array with the elements sorted.

Array.toSpliced.description: Returns a new array with elements removed or added at specified positions.

Array.with.description: Returns a new array with a specified element at a specified index.

Array.toLocaleString.description: Returns a localized string representation of the array.

Array.toString.description: Returns a string representation of the array.
